x4freetext: LANSCE
800-MeV proton (typically 1.6 uA,
1.8 usec micropulse spacing, 625 usec, ~200 psec
mucropulse width, macropulse width, and
40 macropulses/sec) on water-cooled W target
(3 cm in diam., 7 cm long).
Telescopes consisting a gas proportional counter,
a Si surface-barrier detector (500 um thick) and
CsI(Tl) scintillator (3 cm thick) at 20, 60, 90 and
135 deg.
for neutron fluence determination at 16.32 m
from the source
The resolution of the gas counters was not sufficient
to separate isotopes of hydrogen ions or to separate
3He from alpha particles.
(See also p.1082, bottom,left of the 2007 article).
By authors:
